---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Evie and the creative purpose of Evielution." currentPath="/about">
  <section class="page-intro panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">About Evie</p>
    <h1>A musician, composer, and multi-directional creative thinker.</h1>
    <p>
      Evie works across music, writing, games, worldbuilding, and other evolving ideas. Evielution exists to gather
      those threads into one warm, explorable place instead of leaving them scattered across devices, notebooks, and
      half-finished platforms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="two-column">
    <div class="panel stack">
      <h2>How the site thinks</h2>
      <p>
        The site is organized like a map, but underneath it uses a simple, maintainable content structure. That means
        the experience can stay whimsical without becoming fragile.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="panel stack">
      <h2>What matters most</h2>
      <p>
        Warmth, curiosity, and connection. The goal is not to look corporate. The goal is to feel human, welcoming,
        and alive.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
